- cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) is also a likely category as the paper analyzes social structures and communication patterns within corporate networks. 
- cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy) is a possible category as the paper may touch upon security and privacy concerns related to interlocking directorates and close communication within corporate networks. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper may use network analysis algorithms to study the corporate network data. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a less likely category as the paper does not seem to focus on cryptography or security specifically, but may touch upon related topics.
